column1: Deceased in Austria by calendar week (excl. abroad) from 2000
column2: -) Important note Data of weekly deaths for 2000 to 2019 are final. For 2020, data are still preliminary. For the most two recent weeks, data include estimations, since at the time of publication not all deaths were made available to Statistics Austria by the Civil Registry Offices. Deaths of Austrian residents abroad are not included in the data of any published year. Please note that the sum of all 52 or 53 weeks in a given year does not equal the total number of deaths of the respective calendar year. In cases where January 1st is a Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday, the first calendar week also includes the remaining days of the last calendar week of the previous year. Likewise, if the 31st of December is a Thursday, Friday or Saturday, the last calendar week also includes the first day(s) of the successive year. .) Origin of data and legal foundations Statistics Austria processes all deaths delivered by the Civil Registry Offices. Within the publication deadline not all deaths are available, yet. Therefore, the reported deaths of the three most recent weeks include estimations. For this, the empirical delays of the past years were employed to model the expected delays in the reported figures. The underlying estimation model is evaluated weekly and adjusted if necessary. In any case, these preliminary results are subject to uncertainty and the final numbers can be slightly higher or slightly lower than currently estimated. Upon publication, a minimum of 90% of all reported deaths are available to Statistics Austria for any given week and therefore estimations constitute a maximum of 10%. .) Update Preliminary data for 2020 will be updated weekly during the ongoing Corona crisis. Every week, deaths for a new week will be published; at the same time, results for previous weeks will be updated (revised). .)
